Live TV.name: NTV Bangla

Live TV.name: Great Commission TV
Live TV.info: Cignal TV is the single, largest satellite-based cable TV in the Philippines, with a nationwide scope. Its wide scope provides opportunity for GCTV to reach millions of Filipino homes with the Gospel of Christ.

Live TV.name: Kapamilya Channel
Live TV.info: Kapamilya Channel HD is the high-definition (HD) version of the Kapamilya Channel, a 24-hour pay TV channel in the Philippines owned and operated by ABS-CBN Corporation.

Live TV.name: MOR Entertainment
Live TV.info: MOR Entertainment (stylized as MORe) is the digital evolution of MOR (My Only Radio) by ABS-CBN, rebranded on February 14, 2021. It arose after the shutdown of MOR’s FM stations and carries forward the brand’s spirit in a fully online format .

Live TV.name: TFC Asia
Live TV.info: TFC Asia is the Asia-Pacific distribution of The Filipino Channel—offered via cable, satellite, IPTV, and streaming apps—bringing ABS-CBN’s full suite of entertainment and news to Filipinos abroad, with flexible access in HD, live, and on-demand formats.

Live TV.name: CinemaOne
Live TV.info: Cinema One is your go‑to channel for quality Filipino cinema—constantly evolving since the ’90s, topping cable ratings, celebrating indie voices through Cinema One Originals, and expanding online. Whether on cable, Cignal, TV5, or iWantTFC, it’s “laging kasama” for movie lovers!

Live TV.name: CRUNCHYROLL
Live TV.info: Crunchyroll is the go-to anime streaming service for fans—offering a huge, constantly updated library, simulcasts, offline viewing, and community features. In the Philippines, plans are affordable and accessible via various payment methods.

Live TV.name: GMA Pinoy TV
Live TV.info:
A 24/7 international pay-TV channel launched in March 2005, targeting Filipino diaspora globally  .

Offers popular GMA Network shows, movies, news, public affairs, and special events, typically on a one-episode delay  .

Available via cable/satellite worldwide and streaming as part of iWantTFC’s “GMA Pinoy Bundle” since May 2023.

Live TV.name: GMA7 (GMA Network)
Live TV.info:
GMA7 (GMA Network)

The flagship free-to-air television station in the Philippines, home to top-rated programs like 24 Oras, Kapuso Mo, Jessica Soho, teleseryes, variety, and entertainment complexes.

Live TV.name: GMA News TV (now GTV International)
Live TV.info:
GMA News TV (now GTV International)

Launched February 2011 as a news/public affairs channel  .

Rebranded domestically to GTV in February 2021, shifting towards a mix of news, entertainment, and sports  .

Still available internationally under the same name, offering news and public affairs to overseas audiences.

Live TV.name: GMA Life TV
Live TV.info:
Launched in February 2008 as a lifestyle and infotainment channel  .

Airs travel, cooking, health, beauty, talk shows, documentaries, and re-runs of GMA/ GTV lifestyle content.

Live TV.name: OneSports (formerly 5 Plus/ESPN5/Sports5)
Live TV.info:
A Philippine free-to-air sports channel owned by Nation Broadcasting Corp. and operated jointly with TV5/Search & MediaQuest.

Shows include PBA, NBA, UAAP (Finals), PVL, NCAA, FIBA, ONE Championship, UFC, boxing, WWE, e-sports, and more.

Broadcasts are on free TV (UHF 41 in Manila) and Cignal Play; its pay-TV version is called One Sports+, offering 24/7 sports content via Cignal.

Live TV.name: TV5 'HD'
Live TV.info:
The main free-to-air general entertainment network of TV5 Network, part of the MediaQuest group (alongside One Sports).

Offers news, entertainment, sports, drama, and reality content; often carries One Sports events.

Live TV.name: ANIPLUS
Live TV.info:
A regional anime channel (Korean-based) airing licensed anime; limited online info Philippines-specific.

Often bundled in satellite/cable anime packs but requires direct search for local availability.

Live TV.name: Jeepney TV
Live TV.info:
Focused on classic ABS‑CBN series, nostalgia programming—old teleseryes, variety, kids’ shows.

Not covered in latest results but widely available on cable, iWantTFC, and free-to-air via A2Z.

Live TV.name: SCREAMFLIX
Live TV.info:
A horror movie channel launched in mid‑2022, replacing ETC on selected Philippine cable providers  .

Features Asian, European, and Hollywood horror films—slashers, paranormal, psychological thrillers.

Live TV.name: ANIMAX
Live TV.info:
Animax

A dedicated anime channel operating in Asia for nearly 20 years  .

Provides blockcasts, simulcasts of titles from Japan like One Punch Man, Cells at Work!, Seven Deadly Sins, etc.  .

Available on Cignal (e.g., Ch. 46), MySKY plans, and TrueID for streaming  .

Movies.name: Hope for What We Do Not See
Movies.info: The ancient man Job faced tests of integrity that involved a series of tragic events. Look in on the life of the Bannister family as they experience similar tests of integrity in a modern-day setting. In the end, what helped them get their perspective?

Movies.name: Remember the Wife of Lot ​— Part 1
Movies.info:
This video is based on the Bible account of Lot and his family found in Genesis chapters 18 and 19. Jehovah rescued Lot, his wife, and their daughters from the destruction of the wicked cities of Sodom and Gomorrah. However, Lot’s wife looked back despite God’s clear command not to—and she was turned into a pillar of salt (Genesis 19:26).

Jesus later reminded his followers of this event, saying:
“Remember the wife of Lot.” —Luke 17:32.

This serves as a powerful warning for us today:

Don’t look back at the world with longing.

Don’t let material things or past lifestyles distract us.

Stay obedient and focused on Jehovah’s direction, especially as the end of this system draws near.

Movies.name: PBO
Movies.info:
📺 What is PBO?

PBO (Pinoy Box Office) is a 24/7 Filipino cable movie channel.

It specializes in showing Tagalog movies, particularly those produced by Viva Films and other local film companies.

It is owned and operated by Viva Communications, one of the biggest entertainment companies in the Philippines.
